2026-03-13T21:52:46.349Z JOY-005B comment.added "Dispatch concept documented in docs/dev/vision/README.md. Joy status gates trigger Jot todo creation in the target user's repo via joyint.com dispatch service. The source field on the Jot todo links back to the Joy origin item (e.g. source: joy:JOY-002A). When the dispatched Jot todo is completed, joyint.com signals the Joy project that the gate is satisfied. Same mechanism for human reviewers (via CalDAV / jot ls) and AI agents (via jot ls --mine). Neither tool needs to understand the other's full data model -- the source field and the dispatch service are the only coupling points." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-13T22:00:06.435Z JOY-0068 item.created "Vision document as part of a joy product" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-13T22:01:22.970Z JOY-0068 comment.added "Two-phase approach: (1) Template: joy init --vision or joy vision init creates a structured vision.md in .joy/ with sections like target audience, problem, solution, principles. No AI needed, useful immediately. Could fit into MS-02 or earlier. (2) AI-assisted: joy ai vision in MS-05 (Agent Mode). AI reads repo, items, milestones and generates/updates the vision document. Or conducts an interactive interview with the product creator. The template phase provides the structure that the AI phase later maintains." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-13T22:04:03.474Z JOY-0068 comment.added "Refined to three-phase approach: (1) Template: joy vision init creates an empty structured vision.md in .joy/ with section headings. Minimal, immediate value. (2) Interview: joy vision init --interactive walks the user through each section with guided questions and examples (like npm init). No AI needed, but produces a well-filled document. Builds on the same template structure from phase 1. (3) AI-assisted: joy ai vision in MS-05 reads repo context (items, milestones, code) and generates or updates the vision. Can also conduct an AI-driven interview. Builds on the template structure from phases 1-2." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
